race.comment: I'M A DEXSTAR (1) has been racing in town, finishing only a few lengths from the winner fresh before being safely held last time. Strips fitter and with the claim looks very hard to beat this company. TYDEUS (3) resumed from a long break at Lock and scored. Returns to home track now and does boast a good second-up record. Worth following up. ALCANNABIE (4) is fitter for two runs back and finished fifth behind TYDEUS last time. Meets him worse at the weights but has a good third-up record and rates a leading player this line-up. MCKEEVER (2) resumes from a long break. Goes well fresh and should give a sight from a middle draw. CHIARO (10) doesn't win out of turn but ran well enough at Lock and strips fitter. Will give a sight at odds.
